                                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13606Geta">ጌታ፡</persName> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13607Mestiru">ምስጢሩ፡</persName>
                                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13596WaldaG"><roleName type="title">ጋሻዬ፡</roleName> ወልደ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡</persName> 
                                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13597BahrS"><roleName type="title">አቤቶ፡</roleName>
                                            ባሕር፡ ሰገድ፡</persName> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13598Eskender"><roleName type="title">አቤቶ፡</roleName> እስክንድር።</persName> በቀረውም፡ ካህናቱና፡ ፈላሾች።</q>
                                </item>
                                
                                <item xml:id="a4">
                                    <locus target="#2r"/>
                                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">The note states that the manuscript belongs to the church of 
                                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0101MadhaneAlam">Madḫāne ʿĀlam</placeName>.</desc>
                                    <q xml:lang="gez">ስንክሳር፡ ዘ<placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0101MadhaneAlam">ቅዱስ፡ መድኃኔ፡ ዓለም።</placeName>
                                    </q>
                                </item>
                                
                                <item xml:id="e1">
                                    <locus target="#1r"/>
                                    <desc>The first lines of <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4035SenkessarDL">Sǝnkǝssār (Second revision, Dabra Libānos
          recension)</ref> are copied in the upper half of column a, probably as pen trial.</desc>
                                </item>
                                
                                <item xml:id="e2">
                                    <desc>The name <foreign xml:lang="gez">የማነ፡ ክርስቶስ፡</foreign>, probably referring to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10233Yamana">Yamāna Krǝstos</persName>, had been mentioned throughout
                                        in supplications, but has been altered everywhere into <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13599BetaK">Beta Krǝstos</persName>.</desc>
                                </item>
                                
                                <item xml:id="e3">
                                    <locus target="#34r"/>
                                    <desc>The word <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኑናብርዮን፡</foreign> is written in the upper margin of the first page of Ṭǝqǝmt, decorated with dotted lines.
                                    Possibly this may refer to the month of November.</desc>
                                </item>
                            </list>
                            
                        </additions>
                        
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="false" xml:id="binding">
                                <decoNote xml:id="b1" type="Boards">Two wooden boards.</decoNote> 
                                <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="Cover">Blind-tooled leather <term key="quarterCover" ana="#quarterCover">quarter cover</term>
                                    (with the gilded title and shelfmark on the spine).</decoNote> 
                                <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="bindingMaterial">
                                    <material key="wood"/>
                                    <material key="leather"/>
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="SewingStations">4</decoNote> 
                                <decoNote xml:id="b5" type="SewingStations">Sewing stations are used in an irregular way.</decoNote> 
                                <decoNote xml:id="b6">The manuscript has been rebound in the library. Possibly both wooden boards have been replaced, 
                                    and a blind-tooled quarter cover added.</decoNote>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                    
                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            
                            <origDate notBefore="1607" notAfter="1632" evidence="lettering"/>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>The manuscript had very probably belonged to a church in the <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName> area, 
                            from where it was taken by
                            <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9430Tewodros">Tewodros</persName> and brought to <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0101MadhaneAlam">Madḫāne ʿĀlam</placeName>. It was then looted 
                            by the British <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7484Napier">Napier</persName> expedition in <date>1868</date>.
                        </provenance>
                        
                    </history>
                    
